    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    AvailableTitlesPanel
    A panel that displays all Book entities that have at least one "Available" copy.
    Book
    Represents a book entity in the library system.
    BookDaoImpl
    DAO implementation for managing Book entities.
    BookManagementPanel
    A panel that displays and manages Book entities, along with options to add, edit, or delete books.
    BookTests
    Test class for Book entity CRUD operations and associated copies.
    Borrowing
    Represents a record of a user borrowing a copy of a book.
    BorrowingDaoImpl
     
    BorrowingHistoryPanel
    A panel to display the borrowing history for a specific user.
    BorrowingManagementPanel
    A panel that manages the creation, editing, and deletion of Borrowing entities.
    BorrowingTests
     
    CopiesTests
     
    Copy
    Represents a physical copy of a Book in the library.
    CopyDaoImpl
    DAO implementation for managing Copy entities.
    Dao<T>
    A generic DAO (Data Access Object) interface providing basic CRUD operations.
    JPAUtil
    Utility class to provide a shared EntityManagerFactory for the "LibraryPU", and a method to obtain an EntityManager.
    Librarian
    Represents a librarian, specialized from User (1-to-1 link).
    LibrarianDaoImpl
    DAO implementation for the Librarian entity.
    LibrarianTests
     
    LibraryTitlesPanel
    A panel that displays all books in the library, regardless of their availability.
    MainFrame
    The main application frame for the Library System, which can be shown either in librarian mode or in regular user mode.
    Publisher
    Represents a publisher of books.
    PublisherDaoImpl
    DAO implementation for managing Publisher entities.
    PublisherTests
     
    RelationshipIntegrationTests
     
    User
    Represents a general user in the library system.
    UserDaoImpl
    DAO implementation for managing User entities.
    UserManagementPanel
    A panel for managing User entities (adding, editing, deleting).
    UserTests
